      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>NICE BUT NOT EQUAL</font>, By Theeo lowjen</b><br><br>First off I am not whining...I am actually glad to see SOME kind of Pally epic weapon finally being correctly implemented for once.  But compared to all the other weapons effects, ours is the weakest.  150dd?  C'mon.  The Druids get 1650 DoT.  Necros....1100 DoT.  We won't even go into the Warrior epic weapon.  Seems like we will never get a 300 pointer like we should.  Even thought the ORIGINAL Fiery had a level 34 Wizard spell that was supposed to hit for 280 as a proc...it now only hits for a little over 100.  Gimme a break. Make it right or don't make it at all.  Verant stinks *plugs nose and rolls eyes<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>PROC</font>, By Geen</b><br><br>My only complaint is the proc, it does maybe 40 more damage then FA proc, and even though it's fire based, the few people who have a FD say it's resisted ALOT, to the point that it's most likly bugged.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>PROC</font>, By Tuvas </b><br><br>Check out Paladins of Norrath for the pics. One of the paladins is saying the proc isn't what is shown in the spdat file it's a flame DoT which kinda makes more sense. Won't know til I get mine some time, but they are saying its a awesome proc not the lame one shown.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>ABOUT HASTE!!</font>, By Luminarie - sol ro</b><br><br>I just wanna fill you all in just incase some of you didn't know this but ONYL 1 haste item will work at a time and the one with the highest haste is the only one that will work if you have more then 1 item on, and all haste items are stackable with haste spells and that guy who said the delay of this weap could go down to the low 30's high 20's think again it could go as low as 22 and any paladin that has this DEFINATELY has a haste item and almost 90% likely to have someone who can cast haste on him<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>CORRECT HASTE RESULTS...</font>, By Cilinak</b><br><br>One note on the previous post.  Haste does not lower delay.  It increases your attack rate.  What this means stat wise is if a person with 100% haste were to use this weapon (35/40) it would essentially function as a 35/20 weapon.  With 50% the weapon would be akin to a 35/30 weapon.  Still impressive though.<br><hr size='1'></td>
